headlines.description: With Philadelphia swept up in a Super Bowl frenzy, No. 1 Villanova showed again why city sports fans can also brag about having the top team in college basketball. Just across the street from where the Eagles clinched a Super Bowl berth, the Wildcats...
headlines.shortLinkText: Paschall scores 17, leads No. 1 Villanova past Providence

headlines.description: Devon Hall scored 14 points, Kyle Guy had 12 and No. 2 Virginia broke open a close game with an 18-2 run in the second half to win their 11th straight, 61-36 over No. 18 Clemson on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hall, Guy lead No. 2 Virginia past No. 18 Clemson, 61-36

headlines.description: Wendell Carter Jr. had 23 points and 12 rebounds, and No. 4 Duke beat Wake Forest 84-70 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 4 Duke forces 21 turnovers, beats Wake Forest 84-70

headlines.description: Trae Young had 26 points and nine assists, and No. 12 Oklahoma rallied to beat No. 5 Kansas 85-80 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young's 26 help No. 12 Oklahoma top No. 5 Kansas 85-80

video.headline: Oklahoma finishes strong to beat Kansas

headlines.description: Keenan Evans scored 22 of his 26 points after halftime, and No. 14 Texas Tech rallied from a 15-point deficit to beat Oklahoma State 75-70 on Tuesday night and avoid a third straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 14 Texas Tech has big rally to beat Oklahoma State 75-70

video.headline: Culver throws down the hammer for Texas Tech

headlines.description: Jordan Bowden scored 19 points, Lamonte' Turner hit a huge 3-pointer and No. 22 Tennessee nearly blew a 20-point second-half lead before hanging on for a 67-62 victory over Vanderbilt on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 22 Tennessee hangs on to beat Vanderbilt 67-62

headlines.description: Daryl Macon sank three 3-pointers in the second overtime and scored 25 points, lifting Arkansas to an 80-77 win over Georgia on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Macon's late 3s power Arkansas past Georgia, 80-77 in 2 OTs

headlines.description: Freshman Luka Garza scored 17 points with a career-high 16 rebounds, Tyler Cook added 17 points and Iowa walloped Wisconsin 85-67 on Tuesday night, snapping a two-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garza, Cook lead Iowa past Wisconsin 85-67

headlines.description: Trey Landers scored 16 points, Jalen Crutcher made a key 3-pointer and Dayton held off Davidson 65-64 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Crutcher's 3 helps Dayton hold off Davidson 65-64

headlines.description: Jimond Ivey scored 11 of his 17 points in the final six minutes and Akron held off Ohio 71-68 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ivey helps Akron hold off Ohio 71-68

headlines.description: Jeremy Harris scored 20 of his 22 points in the second half and grabbed a career-high 14 rebounds to help Mid-American Conference leader Buffalo beat Eastern Michigan 83-69 on Tuesday night for its eighth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Buffalo wins 8th straight, tops Eastern Michigan 83-69

headlines.description: Nike Sibande scored a career-high 22 points and made all four of his 3-point shots as Miami (Ohio) defeated Central Michigan 70-61 Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sibande's 22 helps Miami (Ohio) top Central Michigan 70-61

headlines.description: Tre'Shaun Fletcher scored 22 points, Jaelan Sanford added 21 and made a key block late to help Toledo beat Western Michigan 85-81 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fletcher, Sanford lead Toledo past Western Michigan 85-81

headlines.description: Kevin Zabo scored seven of his 21 points in overtime and Danny Pippen finished with a double-double to power Kent State to an 88-80 victory over Ball State on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zabo's hot hand in OT lifts Kent State over Ball State 88-80

headlines.description: Keith Hayes poured in 31 points, knocking down 5 of 7 3-pointers, and grabbed seven rebounds to help Division II William Jewell roll to an 86-74 victory over Missouri-Kansas City on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hayes sparks D-II William Jewell past UMKC 86-74

headlines.description: Dimencio Vaughn scored 20 points with 13 rebounds and his extra effort underneath the basket paid off with the game-winner Tuesday night as Rider edged Fairfield 90-88 in a wild finish.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rider finishes on 8-0 run, tips Fairfield 90-88

headlines.description: Chris Clemons and Marcus Burk each made 10 3-pointers as Campbell set a program and Big South Conference game record with 23 3s in its 94-85 victory over Liberty on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clemons, Burk score 74 combined; Campbell hits 23 3s

headlines.description: Albert Owens was one of three Oral Roberts players to notch a double-double with 22 points and a career-high 13 rebounds, and the Golden Eagles beat Division III East Texas Baptist 93-66 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Oral Roberts has 3 players with double-doubles in win

headlines.description: Darrell Brown scored 20 points with eight assists, Elijah Childs added 12 points with 12 rebounds and Bradley pulled away in the second half to defeat Missouri State 72-52 Tuesday night, maintaining a perfect record on its home court this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown helps Bradley top Missouri State 72-52; 11-0 at home

headlines.description: Eugene German didn't miss a shot and finished with 19 points as Northern Illinois routed Bowling Green 93-62 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: German helps Northern Illinois rout Bowling Green 93-62

headlines.description: Deandre Burnett scored 24 points, Terence Davis and Markel Crawford both scored 15 and Mississippi beat Alabama 78-66 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Burnett's 24 points lead Mississippi over Alabama 78-66

video.headline: Hymon uses one hand for putback slam

headlines.description: Marcus Foster had 24 points and eight rebounds, Khyri Thomas added 19 points and seven boards, and Creighton got its third straight season sweep of St. John's with a 68-63 victory on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Creighton gets 3rd straight season sweep of St John's 68-63

headlines.description: Bryant McIntosh and Vic Law scored 18 points apiece for Northwestern, leading a spirited comeback from a 10-point deficit in the first half to beat reeling Minnesota 77-69 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Northwestern rallies past Minnesota 77-69 for season sweep

headlines.description: Duop Reath scored 21, Tremont Waters added 15 points and LSU snapped a three-game skid with a 77-65 victory over Texas A&M on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Reath, Waters lead LSU past Texas A&M, 77-65

headlines.description: PJ Washington had a career-high 22 points, Kevin Knox scored 19 with four 3-pointers and Kentucky pulled away late for a 78-65 victory over Mississippi State Tuesday night to end a two-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kentucky beats Mississippi State 78-65 to end 2-game slide

video.headline: Kentucky's Diallo hits sick crossover on his way to the rim

headlines.description: De'Riante Jenkins coolly nailed a 3-pointer from the top of the circle as VCU tied the game at the end of regulation, and Justin Tillman scored six of his 25 points in overtime as the Rams rallied to edge Saint Louis 75-74 Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tillman, Jenkins help VCU edge Saint Louis 75-74, OT

headlines.description: Alessandro Lever scored 25 points, Joshua Braun had 22 and Grand Canyon rolled to a 96-80 victory over NAIA member William Jessup on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grand Canyon beats NAIA's William Jessup 96-80

headlines.description: Bryson Williams tossed in 20 points on 10-of-14 shooting and Terrell Carter II added 18 points, six rebounds and a pair of blocked shots in the final seconds to help Fresno State hold off UNLV 69-63 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williams, Carter lead Fresno State past UNLV 69-63

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.
nowFeed.story: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
